client.model

Class Bank

  • java.lang.Object
    • client.model.Bank

  • public class Bank
extends java.lang.Object
    The Bank class holds resource cards that are available to the players. These are cards that no player currently has.
    Domain: Each resource must be between 0 and 19
    Author:
    Epper Marshall, Joe Eklund

      • hasResource

        public boolean hasResource(ResourceType resource)
        This method checks whether the bank has enough resources as specified in the parameter
        Parameters:
        resource: - resource is a class that has values for all five possible resources
        Precondition:
        none
        Postcondition:
        This method returns a boolean: true if the bank has the amount of resources specified, false if the bank does not have the amount of resources specified.
